{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"Thomas Grelley I","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Thomas Grelley I","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Thomas"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"Grelley"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Suffix","value":"I"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Lord Thomas de Grelley","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1210–1262","fullLifespan":"about 1210–Bef 18 February 1262","birthDate":"+1210","userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography\nBirth«/b»\nThomas Grelle was the son of Robert by his wife, the daughter of Henry de Lonchamp, the brother of William, the Lord Chancellor to the king.\n\nThomas, son and heir, did his homage and had livery of all his lands.\n\n«b»Career«/b»\n26 Hen III, Thomas was summoned with others to fit himself with horse and armes, and attend the king into France, which he gave C marcs above his ordinary scutage to be freed from that journey.\n\nThe next year he was in the King's service beyond the sea, he was quit of his service of Castlegard to the Castle of Lane.\n\nHe was summoned to fit himself with horse and armes and to repair to the king at Chhester upon Monday next preceding the feast of St. Jo. the Baptist, to withstand the incursions of the Welsh.\n\nHe was constituted warden of the king's forests south of Trent.\n\n«b»Death«/b»\nThomas died in 46 Hen 3 or before.\n\nHis son Peter was not enfeoffed of his Manor of Manchester in Con Lancaster. The custody did appertain to the king by the minority of his heir, so held it in capite by barony, the sheriff had command to seis it.\n\n«b»Heir«/b»\nRobert dyed in 12 Ed. I. whereupon Amadeus de Sauoy had the custody of the manor of Manchester during the minority of Thomas, his son and heir.\n\nRobert, his son and heir, who in 8 Ed. I, having wedded Hawis, one of the daughters and co-heirs of John de Burgo, son of Herbert de Burgo, sometimes Earl of Kent.\n\nHawis had livery of her purportion of her father's land, and the manors of Wakeley, Kingston, and Portelade.","sourceList":[{"title":" The Barony of Grelley in The Victoria history of the county of Lancaster","sourceType":"DEFAULT","sourceLink":"https://archive.org/details/victoriahistoryo01farruoft/page/326/mode/2up","sourceUri":"Q878-QX5"}],"events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"1","year":"1210","date":"about 1210"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1220","date":"Abt 1220","place":"Manchester, Lanc, Engl","type":"Spousal","age":"10","id":"M858-R9W"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1220","date":"1220","place":"Somme, Picardie, France","age":"10","id":"L62S-BWQ"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1228","date":"about 1228","place":"Manchester, Lancashire, England","age":"18","id":"9CD4-RZN"},{"name":"Other","sources":"0","year":"1230","date":"liv abt 1230","place":"England","type":"USER_DEFINED","age":"20"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1230","date":"about 1230","place":"Manchester, Lancashire, England","age":"20","id":"KHY1-K9J"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1230","date":"1230","place":"Manchester, Lancashire, England","age":"20","id":"K867-FSF"},{"name":"Death of Child","sources":"0","year":"1261","date":"1261","place":"Lancashire, England","age":"51","id":"9CD4-RZN"},{"name":"Death","sources":"1","year":"1262","date":"Bef 18 February 1262","age":"52"}],"parent":[{"name":"Robert Grelley","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1173–1230","birthDate":"A+1173","deathDate":"+1230","age":57,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/x5m7e/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"K867-FSF","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/K867-FSF/robert-grelley-1173-1230","published":true},{"name":"Margaret Longchamp","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1179–1220","birthDate":"+1179","deathDate":"+1220","age":41,"portrait":{"url":"https://tree-portraits-pgp.familysearchcdn.org/j9kjj/thumb64.jpg","@type":"ImageObject"},"@type":"Pers