:"Manchester, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Grelley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Possibly an altered form of Irish   Crilly  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Crilly","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Liam.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Raghailligh</b> ‘son of <i>Raghailleach</i>’. Compare   Crawley  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Grelley I was born about 1210, his father, Robert Grelley, was 39 and his mother, Margaret Longchamp, was 32. He married Christina Ledet about 1220, in Manchester, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died before 18 February 1262."},"et":{"about 1210–Bef 18 February 1262":"umbes 1210–enne 18. veebruari 1262","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1201–1271":"1201–1271","1228–1261":"1228–1261","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1179–1220":"1179–1220","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1261":"1261","1173":"1173","1271":"1271","Bef 18 February 1262":"enne 18. veebruari 1262","1228":"1228","about 1228":"umbes 1228","liv abt 1230":"umbes 1230","1179":"1179","1201":"1201","Abt 1220":"umbes 1220","1210":"1210","about 1210":"umbes 1210","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Manchester, Lancashire, England":"Manchester, Lancashire, Inglismaa,